  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DARP IFC/ADM Cornerstone Facility</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By providing sound, but financially stressed, companies with access to financing which they would not otherwise be able to access using conventional banking avenues, the Facility would:  i) support viable private sector companies; ii) save jobs; iii) increase efficiency; and iv) maintain productive asset utilization.  Investing in stressed companies with the aim of corporate turnaround and recovery, has a high development impact in improving corporate governance and transparency of investee companies as well as inducing managerial and operational improvements required to restore viability to the investee company.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project, DARP IFC/ADM Lending Facility (the Facility), aims to set up a lending facility platform that will invest in small to mid cap companies in Asia, targeting stressed and turnaround investments.  The Facility would extend loans to companies with strong fundamentals but facing difficulty raising new financing due to financial imbalances or inability to access conventional bank financing avenues.  The objective of the Facility would be to provide funding to otherwise sound companies and position them for growth in the aftermath of the recent crisis.   ADM Capital (ADM Capital) will act as the Facility agent to source, structure, execute, and supervise the investments made under the Facility.</narrative>
  </description>
